{
  "stem": "24212.5",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "To live-- not every day, but every hour, every minute, every second-- that you don't know whether in next moment you won't be marching up the chimney [POINTING] or being shot or die of typhoid fever or something.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Nobody can convey that.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, yes I, I definitely do.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that was the reason why I am teaching a course of the same title as my book is.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And maybe if you'll allow me, I will read that from, from the book, all right.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] This is called And I must show off this fabulous picture of a woman on a swastika, which I think expresses it very well.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And what I'm going to read you are just a few sentences from the epilogue to the books-- to the book. 'Celebrate life as much as you can, without hurting others.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "For too much of it has been wasted through sheer madness.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Place flowers of sympathy and sorrow on the non-existent graves of millions who were annihilated through cruelty and with malice of forethought.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Keep in mind the victims of the Holocaust and their bones scattered all over Europe, unmarked with crosses or David's stars.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "For lest you forget, their sacrifices will have been in vain, and humanity will tumble into the abyss of evil again.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Honor the memory of those fallen and strengthen your soul against repeated bereavement of mankind, so that you can look with a clear conscience into the eyes of your children.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Weep not for the survivors of the purgatory called Holocaust.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "For theirs is the ultimate glory in triumph.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They outlived the evil of their tormentors.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And by their very lives, overcame it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Learn from them.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
